
    THE late SABC sports presenter, Cebo Manyaapelo, was described yesterday as a person who loved his job.Speaker after speaker testified to this during a memorial service for the 50-year-old at the broadcaster’s regional offices in Mahikeng, North West.People came in large numbers to celebrate the life of the broadcasting giant, who died last Wednesday after a long illness.Motsweding FM sports producer Lesego Sewai said: “Death robbed us of a talented and knowledgeable sports commentator. He was like a father to us and I enjoyed working with him.“We thank God that he gave us someone who would change people’s lives through soccer.”Cebo became a sports commentator on SABC2’s Laduma in 1998 and at the same time started presenting Mamepe a Metshameko on Motsweding FM. He had previously worked at Radio Bop and Radio Mmbatho.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvIfEcdAZaiBT1ubp_LYY50tiQqe8PEqEj9w2mp5fdH7-Il7GFAv8q4_lraLUlznqUXkD7RrjEO926zxy-NoEpQw3DxPqbv3d8BCqYsGw-MX1v1jJhw679ncWvTFeWT76LqRvebHBnClvmGGtegg5q6d0wHLzEb5xaUYnwV4l0vWJEhseBCGVyRZzrjhiRYVf3Rix7XE7lYBq8xdqWRqkaDnpCnSY6jmt2KpnPfi_gmIHgxG2L-pGnvSFTgLKLJ3Q-VPisIPzlxdt5v9ivG\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzKFWXH1N1IDbEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
