Photo: Otsile TlapeSpeaking at the service, North West Premier Supra Mahumapelo said: “He was a knowledgeable and gifted radio personality who was admired and respected by listeners young and old.“The province has not only lost a good broadcaster but an entertainer and motivator as well. Our thoughts and prayers are with his family and may his soul rest in peace.”Cebo’s colleague Oshebeng Koonyaditse said he had loved his family a lot.“He would work until late at night in Joburg but always made sure he went home to Mahikeng to be with his family,” he said.“I worked with him for 28 years and I learned a lot from him.”He will be laid to rest in his home town of Mahikeng tomorrow.
